UPDATE public.evaluations
SET evaluator_note = E'Jacky — You are an outstanding Lead, and it is truly exciting to see the standard of leadership you bring to this office.\nYou have a remarkable ability to deliver constructive feedback in a way that is direct yet encouraging — guiding your team toward excellence without diminishing their confidence. That is a skill many leaders work years to develop, and it is evident that it comes naturally to you.\nAs we continue to work together, here are a few focus areas that I believe will further elevate both your leadership and the overall performance of the office:\n\nSchedule Awareness and Preparation\n\nI encourage you to build a habit of briefly reviewing the schedule and operatory notes ahead of time so that your team is well-informed and prepared before patients arrive. A simple heads-up on what is coming goes a long way in keeping things running smoothly and reducing surprises throughout the day.\n\nFloor Presence and One-on-One Connection\n\nWhen time allows, make it a point to walk the floor and check in individually with your RDAs. A brief, genuine connection lets them know you are present and invested in their well-being, and it gives you real-time insight into how the team is doing at any given moment.\n\nRadiograph Quality Control\n\nAs you did when I was present, continue to review radiographs for quality whenever possible. Catching issues early helps avoid multiple retakes, saves time, and upholds the clinical standard the office is known for.\n\nDelegation Before and During Huddle\n\nIf you notice team members standing around before huddle, do not hesitate to assign tasks. Delegation is one of the most powerful tools a lead has — the full weight of the office does not fall on you alone. Direct your staff confidently and trust them to execute.\n\nScale and Measurement Accessibility\n\nI would recommend having an additional scale and measurement tool added to the office and positioned so that it is the very first step before bringing a patient back. With the current setup placing it in the X-ray room, there is risk of this step being overlooked. Making it more accessible will help ensure it is never missed.\n\nOverall, the work being done at this office is exceptional, and you deserve a great deal of credit for that. I am here to support you every step of the way — please never hesitate to reach out. I am genuinely excited to watch you and your team continue to grow and thrive!'
WHERE id = '80226d5a-8efe-4eed-87b9-fe68e4736218';